00:22:18,011 --> 00:22:21,331
The title is "Yellow Flowers Scatter Like Gold."

252
00:22:21,331 --> 00:22:25,991
This question seems simple, and yet it filters so many out.

253
00:22:25,991 --> 00:22:29,510
Most of them take the yellow flowers as chrysanthemums.

254
00:22:29,510 --> 00:22:32,111
They're not aware that it's from the verse,

255
00:22:32,111 --> 00:22:35,430
"The green branches remain as verdant, but yellow flowers scatter like gold."

256
00:22:35,430 --> 00:22:39,310
It wrote about the scenery of Grain Rain around the Spring Equinox.

257
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:42,871
The yellow flower here refers to rapeseed flowers.

258
00:22:42,871 --> 00:22:47,491
If the candidates mistook it as chrysanthemums of the autumn, they're eliminated.

259
00:22:47,491 --> 00:22:49,591
This candidate didn't go off topic.

260
00:22:49,591 --> 00:22:54,091
However, it doesn't rhyme and is poorly written.

261
00:22:54,091 --> 00:22:55,810
Rapeseed flowers in the village.

262
00:22:55,810 --> 00:22:59,571
Day after day, they are busy extracting oil from the rapeseed.

263
00:22:59,571 --> 00:23:02,471
No one cares about poor peasants.

264
00:23:58,051 --> 00:24:00,351
 This is a set of writing tools from a literati in Qingzhou. 

265
00:24:00,351 --> 00:24:01,510
 It's for you. 

266
00:24:01,510 --> 00:24:03,310
 I wish you good luck. 

267
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:55,270
   

268
00:24:55,270 --> 00:24:57,830
The third session is political discourse.

269
00:24:57,830 --> 00:25:00,251
Discourse on subduing border intruders and pacifying the residents.

270
00:25:00,251 --> 00:25:03,171
 Discourse on subduing border intruders and pacifying the residents? 

271
00:25:18,130 --> 00:25:20,011
 But the political discourse in the third session... 

272
00:25:20,011 --> 00:25:22,270
 Tutor Shang approves of your article. Right? 

273
00:25:22,270 --> 00:25:25,550
 He said your idea is unconventional and amb... 

274
00:25:25,550 --> 00:25:27,650
 Ambitious and bold. 

275
00:25:27,650 --> 00:25:31,470
 Yes, he did say my article is ambitious and bold. 

276
00:25:31,470 --> 00:25:37,230
 However, he also said my idea was wild and might be shocking. 

277
00:25:37,230 --> 00:25:42,430
 So, if a rigid and conservative examiner reviews my article, 

278
00:25:42,430 --> 00:25:44,951
 he might give me the lowest grade. 

279
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:47,611
 That's bad. 

280
00:25:50,590 --> 00:25:51,571
 Here's what I'm going to do. 

281
00:25:51,571 --> 00:25:53,151
 In the first session, I'll do what I know. 

282
00:25:53,151 --> 00:25:54,831
 In the second session, I'll do what I can. 

283
00:25:54,831 --> 00:25:56,911
 And in the third session, 

284
00:25:56,911 --> 00:25:59,370
 I think I have to pray to the deity. 

285
00:26:14,491 --> 00:26:15,731
Time's up.

286
00:26:15,731 --> 00:26:17,591
Stop writing.

287
00:26:17,591 --> 00:26:19,990
Turn in your answer sheet.

288
00:26:49,890 --> 00:26:51,991
 They're out. 

289
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:55,070
 Son. 

290
00:26:55,070 --> 00:26:56,790
Young Lady!

291
00:26:58,671 --> 00:26:59,610
 Daughter. 

292
00:26:59,610 --> 00:27:02,110
 - Young Lady. 
 - Juli. 

293
00:27:02,110 --> 00:27:04,270
You're finally out.

294
00:27:06,890 --> 00:27:08,091
 Father! 

295
00:27:08,091 --> 00:27:09,791
What's wrong?

296
00:27:09,791 --> 00:27:12,991
Young Lady, you smell.

297
00:27:13,890 --> 00:27:16,150
That hurts.

298
00:27:16,150 --> 00:27:17,410
I didn't mean to do it.

299
00:27:17,410 --> 00:27:19,551
I'm worried sick about you.

300
00:27:19,551 --> 00:27:21,090
Juli, you know what?

301
00:27:21,090 --> 00:27:23,670
I had a fever three days before I entered the examination hall.

302
00:27:23,670 --> 00:27:26,331
This metropolitan examination gives me a hard time.

303
00:27:26,331 --> 00:27:29,550
Young Lady, did you do well in your exam?

304
00:27:29,550 --> 00:27:31,291
I don't know.

305
00:27:31,291 --> 00:27:34,251
I've done my very best.

306
00:27:34,930 --> 00:27:36,730
By the way, Juli,

307
00:27:37,990 --> 00:27:39,590
let me tell you this.

308
00:27:39,590 --> 00:27:43,170
The political discourse...

309
00:27:44,291 --> 00:27:45,650
Forget it. Let's not talk about it.

310
00:27:45,650 --> 00:27:47,950
I want delicious food now. Do we have any good food at home?

311
00:27:47,950 --> 00:27:50,551
Of course, the food is ready. There are many delicious foods.

312
00:27:50,551 --> 00:27:52,571
- What do we have? 
 - Crispy pork knuckles.

313
00:27:52,571 --> 00:27:53,951
Crispy pork knuckles?

314
00:27:53,951 --> 00:27:55,391
I thought you made it steamed.

315
00:27:55,391 --> 00:27:58,491
This is deviant.

316
00:27:59,170 --> 00:28:02,170
This question is about how to subdue border intruders.

317
00:28:02,170 --> 00:28:06,970
And yet, this discourse wrote about the nurture of enemies on the border.

318
00:28:06,970 --> 00:28:10,630
But I find it sensible after reading it, though.

319
00:28:10,630 --> 00:28:13,450
Sensible? This is ridiculous.

320
00:28:14,890 --> 00:28:16,270
What's with the noise?

321
00:28:16,270 --> 00:28:18,170
Where's your manners?

322
00:28:20,710 --> 00:28:21,931
Your Highness,

323
00:28:21,931 --> 00:28:24,471
we come across a political discourse

324
00:28:24,471 --> 00:28:27,790
and we are having a debate over it.

325
00:28:27,790 --> 00:28:29,130
Bring me the sheet.

326
00:28:29,130 --> 00:28:32,610
My uncle and I will read what's written on it.

327
00:28:36,491 --> 00:28:38,911
Please read this, Uncle.

328
00:28:43,671 --> 00:28:47,191
 Mu Zhuohua is bold to write this. 

329
00:28:47,191 --> 00:28:49,730
 But it does make some sense. 

330
00:28:49,730 --> 00:28:51,771
 It's right that war brings harm to people, and the expenses are high. 

331
00:28:51,771 --> 00:28:54,990
 This method might be feasible. 

332
00:28:55,790 --> 00:28:58,291
Is this candidate from Northern Liang or Eastern Xia?

333
00:28:58,291 --> 00:29:00,731
This person actually takes the outsider's side.

334
00:29:01,691 --> 00:29:03,431
Southern Chen should employ Confucian teachings

335
00:29:03,431 --> 00:29:06,591
to enlighten foreign clans and set it as the national religion,

336
00:29:06,591 --> 00:29:08,930
like the Western Regions do.

337
00:29:09,851 --> 00:29:12,051
If this is a feasible way,

338
00:29:12,051 --> 00:29:16,790
Uncle, what's the meaning of us waging wars all along?

339
00:29:17,731 --> 00:29:19,711
For the opportunity...

340
00:29:20,331 --> 00:29:22,690
to have a say over them.

341
00:29:24,210 --> 00:29:28,411
I think I've seen this handwriting before.

342
00:29:28,411 --> 00:29:33,310
It's similar to the perfect answer of the first session.

343
00:29:33,310 --> 00:29:36,591
This candidate wrote the poor verse yesterday.

344
00:29:36,591 --> 00:29:39,890
This candidate might have a good memory and is insightful.

345
00:29:39,890 --> 00:29:43,471
They could be a compatible rival against Shen Jinghong.

346
00:29:44,370 --> 00:29:47,291
I think this person is just average.

347
00:29:47,291 --> 00:29:49,871
We mustn't let this person pass the examination.

348
00:29:51,541 --> 00:29:53,857
   

349
00:30:02,111 --> 00:30:04,011
Your Highness.

350
00:30:04,011 --> 00:30:05,830
Was it Mu Zhuohua?

351
00:30:05,830 --> 00:30:07,270
Yes.

352
00:30:07,270 --> 00:30:10,650
Lord Ding sent her to the examination hall himself.

353
00:30:10,650 --> 00:30:13,111
All the way from Yanzhou.

354
00:30:13,111 --> 00:30:14,610
Your Majesty,

355
00:30:14,610 --> 00:30:19,271
is she the daughter of one of the deceased warriors like Yun Xiangyue?

356
00:30:19,271 --> 00:30:22,410
The emperor halted my action against Yan'er.

357
00:30:23,591 --> 00:30:27,971
I can't sit by and wait till his lead points to me.

358
00:30:30,631 --> 00:30:33,291
I need to know everything about her.

359
00:30:33,291 --> 00:30:35,291
The more detailed, the better.

360
00:30:35,291 --> 00:30:37,610
- Start investigating. 
 - Yes.

361
00:30:44,291 --> 00:30:45,650
Merciful deity,

362
00:30:45,650 --> 00:30:47,170
I did nothing wrong.

363
00:30:47,170 --> 00:30:51,450
Everything I've done is for the sake of Ju'er and Chen'er.

364
00:30:52,210 --> 00:30:55,011
Sadly, they always take Yan'er's side.

365
00:30:55,011 --> 00:30:57,010
That truly upsets me.

366
00:30:57,010 --> 00:31:00,090
As of now, I have to protect myself too.

367
00:31:00,090 --> 00:31:02,351
Things are getting more difficult for me.

368
00:31:03,491 --> 00:31:06,191
Merciful deity, please.

369
00:31:10,508 --> 00:31:13,170
   

370
00:31:13,170 --> 00:31:15,600
   

371
00:31:23,211 --> 00:31:24,811
 Young Lady! 

372
00:31:27,610 --> 00:31:28,910
Young Lady.

373
00:31:28,930 --> 00:31:33,351
Young Lady, I returned from outside and was told that the results announcement is today.

374
00:31:33,351 --> 00:31:34,970
Is that so?

375
00:31:36,391 --> 00:31:38,291
Young Lady, why aren't you anxious about it?

376
00:31:38,291 --> 00:31:41,231
Everyone is waiting for the announcement. We should go there now.

377
00:31:41,231 --> 00:31:43,330
No, this is beneath me!

378
00:31:43,330 --> 00:31:46,670
The master scholar wouldn't check for their rank by themselves.

379
00:31:46,670 --> 00:31:51,291
They always stay composed and wait for the good news at home.

380
00:31:51,291 --> 00:31:53,431
- Wait for good news at home? 
 - Yeah.

381
00:31:53,431 --> 00:31:54,510
That makes sense.

382
00:31:54,510 --> 00:31:56,251
You're surely the master scholar.

383
00:31:56,251 --> 00:31:58,130
Young Lady, you must stay here and go nowhere.

384
00:31:58,130 --> 00:32:00,951
- Wait for your word of success. 
 - I won't go anywhere. Go ahead.

385
00:32:10,291 --> 00:32:12,390
I mustn't go. No, I can't.

386
00:32:13,170 --> 00:32:17,591
If I fail the examination, I'll be a laughingstock under the announcement board.

387
00:32:18,131 --> 00:32:20,031
Oh, my.

388
00:32:20,970 --> 00:32:22,770
What was wrong with me?

389
00:32:22,770 --> 00:32:26,771
It's apparent that both Lord Ding and First Prince support wars.

390
00:32:26,771 --> 00:32:29,051
Why did I write nonsense like such?

391
00:32:29,051 --> 00:32:30,691
Wait.

392
00:32:30,691 --> 00:32:35,310
Had I written an ingratiating answer that defied my own will,

393
00:32:35,310 --> 00:32:37,991
it wouldn't have been a good answer.

394
00:32:41,091 --> 00:32:42,791
Forget it.

395
00:32:42,791 --> 00:32:44,390
Just let it be.

396
00:32:45,531 --> 00:32:50,951
I'm going to pack my luggage and seek another place to stay.

397
00:32:50,951 --> 00:32:55,590
I will study for another three years and resit for the metropolitan examination.

398
00:32:55,590 --> 00:33:00,011
I can't really ask Lord Ding to support me for three years.

399
00:33:06,650 --> 00:33:08,450
Is she back already?

400
00:33:14,090 --> 00:33:15,951
Miss... Miss Song.

401
00:33:15,951 --> 00:33:18,031
Why are you here?

402
00:33:18,031 --> 00:33:22,750
- Are you feeling unwell? 
 - No, I'm good.

403
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:27,310
Can't I come here to pay you a visit?

404
00:33:27,310 --> 00:33:28,751
Of course, you can.

405
00:33:28,751 --> 00:33:31,030
Miss Song, come on in.

406
00:33:36,510 --> 00:33:38,910
Zhuohua, did you know?

407
00:33:38,910 --> 00:33:42,491
All of the ladies like the scented sachets you gave them.

408
00:33:42,491 --> 00:33:45,650
They'd like to order a dozen from you.

409
00:33:45,650 --> 00:33:48,811
And yet you're leaving soon.

410
00:33:49,710 --> 00:33:53,050
Actually, you can stand on your own feet

411
00:33:53,050 --> 00:33:57,170
in the capital with your healing skill

412
00:33:57,170 --> 00:33:59,930
other than fixating on the examination.

413
00:33:59,930 --> 00:34:04,371
Miss Song, the capital is too lively to be a place to study.

414
00:34:04,371 --> 00:34:07,970
Becoming an official is my life's pursuit.

415
00:34:07,970 --> 00:34:12,210
And I work as a physician just to feed myself.

416
00:34:13,110 --> 00:34:17,951
By the way, Miss Song, I will give you the formula for the scented sachet later.

417
00:34:19,490 --> 00:34:22,731
The imperial examination is a tough journey.

418
00:34:22,731 --> 00:34:27,511
So, don't get upset if you fail it.

419
00:34:28,211 --> 00:34:31,471
Zhuohua, your courage in trying it

420
00:34:31,471 --> 00:34:35,651
has already set you apart from the rest of the women in this era.

421
00:34:35,651 --> 00:34:36,651
Think about it.

422
00:34:36,651 --> 00:34:41,370
Not many people in this world dare put all their eggs in one basket.

423
00:34:41,370 --> 00:34:43,130
It's tough for women...

424
00:34:44,211 --> 00:34:46,290
to live in the current society.

425
00:34:46,290 --> 00:34:52,470
So, I hope you will live your life, come what may. All right?

426
00:34:53,190 --> 00:34:55,370
I will, Miss Song.

427
00:34:58,090 --> 00:34:59,990
Young Lady!

428
00:34:59,990 --> 00:35:02,070
You made it!

429
00:35:02,070 --> 00:35:03,731
Me?

430
00:35:05,530 --> 00:35:06,671
I made it?

431
00:35:06,671 --> 00:35:08,251
Am I the master scholar?

432
00:35:08,251 --> 00:35:10,370
You're overconfident, Young Lady.

433
00:35:10,370 --> 00:35:12,950
The master scholar can only be Young Master Jinghong.

434
00:35:13,930 --> 00:35:15,131
What about me?

435
00:35:15,131 --> 00:35:16,370
My rank?

436
00:35:16,370 --> 00:35:18,590
You won 17th place.

437
00:35:19,050 --> 00:35:20,711
17th place?

438
00:35:20,711 --> 00:35:23,131
Blimey! 17th is a good rank, too.

439
00:35:23,131 --> 00:35:25,450
Great! You really made the cut!

440
00:35:25,450 --> 00:35:28,291
This is what I'm going to do. I'll bring the good news to all the ladies.

441
00:35:29,490 --> 00:35:31,770
- That's great, Young Lady. 
 - 17th? Did you get it right?

442
00:35:31,770 --> 00:35:33,090
Yes, you won 17th place.

443
00:35:33,090 --> 00:35:35,390
I made it! Hurrah!

444
00:35:36,410 --> 00:35:38,091
- This is indeed a great surprise. 
 - Miss Mu made the cut!

445
00:35:38,091 --> 00:35:39,071
She's the 17th.

446
00:35:39,071 --> 00:35:40,291
- 17th? That's great. 
 - Exactly.

447
00:35:40,291 --> 00:35:42,130
- 17th place? 
 - Yes

448
00:35:42,130 --> 00:35:43,811
Come here.

449
00:35:43,811 --> 00:35:45,771
She made it. She won 17th place.

450
00:35:45,771 --> 00:35:47,150
What?

451
00:35:47,150 --> 00:35:49,190
I've been looking for you, Madam Lu.

452
00:35:49,190 --> 00:35:50,551
Zhuohua made the cut.

453
00:35:50,551 --> 00:35:52,711
- Really? 
 - Yes.

454
00:35:53,730 --> 00:35:57,671
Ladies, gather here. Zhuohua made the cut!

455
00:35:57,671 --> 00:36:00,270
I told you. I told you this early.

456
00:36:00,270 --> 00:36:02,950
- People who rent my house come out as great literati. 
 - Rightfully so.

457
00:36:02,950 --> 00:36:05,630
The former was a poet and now is a metropolitan graduate.

458
00:36:05,630 --> 00:36:09,391
 Miss Mu won 17th place. Miss Mu won 17th place. 

459
00:36:09,391 --> 00:36:10,751
Come over.

460
00:36:10,751 --> 00:36:12,170
 She won 17th place! She made the cut! 

461
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:13,391
 Miss Mu won 17th place. 

462
00:36:13,391 --> 00:36:15,291
 Zhuohua! 

463
00:36:15,291 --> 00:36:16,251
 Miss Mu. 

464
00:36:16,251 --> 00:36:18,331
- Miss Song. Madam Lu.  
 - I gathered everyone here
to congratulate you.

465
00:36:18,331 --> 00:36:19,611
You're all here?

466
00:36:19,611 --> 00:36:20,670
I'm so glad for you.

467
00:36:20,670 --> 00:36:22,190
Thank you, Miss Song. Thank you so much.

468
00:36:22,190 --> 00:36:23,611
- Applause! 
 - Thank you so much, ladies.

469
00:36:23,611 --> 00:36:25,151
Thank you so much, ladies.

470
00:36:25,151 --> 00:36:26,491
Thank you.

471
00:36:29,971 --> 00:36:31,371
A woman?

472
00:36:31,910 --> 00:36:34,990
The candidate who wrote about nurturing enemies on the border was a woman?

473
00:36:34,990 --> 00:36:38,851
The candidate who's been on par with Shen Jinghong is actually a woman?

474
00:36:38,851 --> 00:36:42,190
Yes, so it seems.

475
00:36:42,990 --> 00:36:46,210
Mu Zhuohua.

476
00:36:46,791 --> 00:36:48,490
Mu Zhuohua?

477
00:36:48,490 --> 00:36:52,250
This name rings a bell.

478
00:36:52,250 --> 00:36:53,891
Think harder.

479
00:36:58,351 --> 00:36:59,951
I can't recall anything.

480
00:36:59,970 --> 00:37:04,790
But I must find a chance to meet her in person to vent...

481
00:37:04,790 --> 00:37:06,650
To vent my anger.

482
00:37:06,650 --> 00:37:09,331
She actually wrote nonsense.

483
00:37:09,331 --> 00:37:11,670
How could she win 17th place?

484
